prompt:
Add a public class called Point to Domain.calr with a constructor that takes x and y coordinates (i32) and stores them in fields.

Use this exact Calor constructor syntax:
§CL{c001:Point:pub}
  §FLD{i32:_x:priv}
  §FLD{i32:_y:priv}
  §CTOR{pub}
    §I{i32:x}
    §I{i32:y}
    §ASSIGN _x x
    §ASSIGN _y y
  §/CTOR
§/CL{c001}

The §CTOR{visibility}...§/CTOR syntax defines a constructor:
- visibility is pub/priv/prot
- §I{type:name} defines constructor parameters
- Use §ASSIGN to set field values
